Parliament of Catalonia daily sessions

projectDesc.p: ParlaMint is a project that aims to (1) create a multilingual set of comparable corpora of parliamentary proceedings uniformly encoded according to the ParlaMint encoding guidelines, covering the period from 2015 to mid-2022; (2) add linguistic annotations to the corpora and machine-translate them to English; (3) make the corpora available through concordancers; and (4) build use cases in Political Sciences and Digital Humanities based on the corpus data.

prefixDef.p: Private URIs with this prefix point to aligned source elements of the MTed corpus.

div.head: SESSIÓ NÚM. 1
div.note: The session is open at eleven in the morning and two minutes. He chairs the President of the Editorial Board, accompanied by the Secretaries of the Editorial Board, who is assisted by the major reader and the late Pere Sol and Ordis.

u.note: According to Rule 99.2 of the Rules of Procedure, Members are nominally called in alphabetical order to vaginate to the presidential table and place the papers in the ballot box. Members who are members of the Government in office and members of the Education Bureau are called at the end.
It goes to the polls and then to the countdown.
